1. Problem Statement
Before designing the architecture of any software system, the first step is to understand the business problem and gather 
the functional requirements.
For a School Management System, the objective is to manage the complete lifecycle of students, teachers, staff, academics,
 and administrative operations through a centralized system.

2. Core Business Requirements
The following are the basic functional requirements of a School Management System:
Student Admission
Admission Fee Management
Student Registration
Class Assignment
Teacher Assignment
Books & Library Management
Uniform Management
Fee Management
Student Attendance
Teacher Attendance
Timetable & Classes
Examination & Results
Reports & Dashboard
Parent Management
Communication & Notifications